Count Check is a vampyre in the Lumbridge graveyard, south of the church. He advises players to have unique passwords and to enable two-step verification for their registered recovery email. He also checks whether the player has the Authenticator enabled and a Bank PIN.

He also is able to teleport players to the entrance of the Stronghold of Security to learn more about account security, however this can only be done once.

The player may ask Count Check to count for them, prompting him to recite four tips for account security:

  • One... unique password.
  • Two... step email verification.
  • Free... authenticator.
  • Four... digit bank PIN!

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Count Check's name is likely a play on "Account check".
  • When asked to count, he says "free" instead of "three" to indicate that the authenticator is free to set up.
  • Count Check's dialogue is likely a reference to Count von Count on Sesame Street.
  • He is one of only two vampyres in free-to-play worlds, the other being Count Draynor.
  • His in-game model is a slightly recoloured Count Draynor.
